# Cursor Landing repo layout

## What this repository is

A **Cursor Agent skill** users install to `~/.cursor/skills/cursor-landing/`. It prepares **other** repos (brownfield apps) with `CONTEXT.md`, `AGENTS.md`, and `.cursor/rules` — not this folder unless the user is deliberately dogfooding here.

Invoke in target repos: `/cursor-landing` or `/cursor-landing emergency`. This skill uses `disable-model-invocation`; plain English does not load it.

## Directory map

```text
CONTEXT.md, AGENTS.md ← factory maintainer glossary + guardrails (not copied to install bundle)
SKILL.md              ← agent workflow (Phase 0–3, emergency)
README.md, OVERVIEW.md ← human setup and positioning
references/           ← scan checklist, formats, annexes, research, SCAN-REPORT-SCHEMA
assets/               ← templates written into *target* repos (not copied blindly here)
scripts/              ← reserved; checklist-driven scan in v1
.cursor/rules/        ← maintainer rules (`cursor-landing-*.mdc`; dual-publish globs `github-publish-lisp/**`)
Planner/              ← archived planner/router reference from another project; do not edit unless user asks
github-publish/       ← markdown install tree (output of scripts/build-install-bundle.ps1)
github-publish-lisp/  ← pseudo-Lisp v2 ship product (/cursor-landing) — NOT built by that script
```

## Dual publish (mixed architecture)

Factory root is **markdown + JSON**; **`github-publish-lisp/cursor-landing-skill/`** is the **Lisp ship product** (pseudo-Lisp `SKILL.md` + `(scan_report …)`). **Never** copy factory `SKILL.md` into the Lisp tree — port semantics per format. Detail: [.cursor/plans/dual-publish-architecture.md](../plans/dual-publish-architecture.md); globs: [cursor-landing-dual-publish.mdc](cursor-landing-dual-publish.mdc).

## Factory maintainer rules (this repo)

Four **alwaysApply** rules (safety, conduct, repo-layout, skill-workflow) stay short. Three **glob** rules scope detail: `references/**`, human docs, and `.mdc` authoring. This split mirrors the Phase 2 target pattern (thin always-on + evidence-based globs) documented in [references/MDC-RULES-FORMAT.md](../../references/MDC-RULES-FORMAT.md). See [.cursor/MDC-REWRITE-HANDOFF.md](../../.cursor/MDC-REWRITE-HANDOFF.md).

## Factory maintainer files (this repo only)

| Artifact | Rule |
|----------|------|
| `CONTEXT.md` | Factory glossary — not the install bundle; see [references/CONTEXT-FORMAT.md](../../references/CONTEXT-FORMAT.md) |
| `AGENTS.md` | Factory guardrails + proof — defers Planner-routed work to [Planner/AGENTS.md](../../Planner/AGENTS.md) |
| `.cursor/rules/cursor-landing-*.mdc` | Maintainer rules — mirror the Phase 2 target pattern (thin always-on + glob-scoped) |

## Outputs the skill creates (in target repos)

| Artifact | Rule |
|----------|------|
| `CONTEXT.md` | Glossary only — [references/CONTEXT-FORMAT.md](../../references/CONTEXT-FORMAT.md) |
| `AGENTS.md` | Slim guardrails + proof command — [references/AGENTS-FORMAT.md](../../references/AGENTS-FORMAT.md) |
| `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` | Conduct + scoped rules; link CONTEXT — [assets/conduct.template.mdc](../../assets/conduct.template.mdc) |
| `docs/EMERGENCY-HANDOFF.md` | Emergency mode only — transient run-state |

## Do not

- Run full `/cursor-landing` init against this repo and overwrite skill files unless the user explicitly wants a self-migration session.
- Merge host annex content into SKILL.md body (annexes are scan reference only).
- Add MCP servers to this repo by default — inventory/offer only per [references/annexes/mcp.md](../../references/annexes/mcp.md).
- Blind-copy factory root or `github-publish/` files over `github-publish-lisp/` pseudo-Lisp spine (`SKILL.md`, `question-bank.md`, `scan-checklist.md`) — see dual-publish plan above.
